```sql
-- Determine whether Martini's Fine Steakhouse is in danger based on the latest available calendar-month fraud rate
WITH
cte_merchant AS (
  SELECT
    ('Martinis_Fine_Steakhouse') AS merchant
),
cte_tx AS (
  SELECT
    p.merchant,
    (
      make_timestamp(CAST(p.year AS INTEGER), 1, 1, 0, 0, 0)
      + (CAST(p.day_of_year AS INTEGER) - 1) * INTERVAL '1 day'
      + CAST(p.hour_of_day AS INTEGER) * INTERVAL '1 hour'
      + CAST(p.minute_of_hour AS INTEGER) * INTERVAL '1 minute'
    ) AS transaction_ts,
    COALESCE(p.eur_amount, 0.0) AS eur_amount,
    COALESCE(p.has_fraudulent_dispute, FALSE) AS has_fraudulent_dispute
  FROM uploads.main.payments p
  JOIN cte_merchant m
    ON p.merchant = m.merchant
  WHERE COALESCE(p.is_refused_by_adyen, FALSE) = FALSE
),
cte_fraud_per_month AS (
  SELECT
    merchant,
    DATE_TRUNC('month', transaction_ts) AS month,
    SUM(eur_amount) AS total_volume_eur,
    SUM(CASE WHEN has_fraudulent_dispute THEN eur_amount ELSE 0.0 END) AS fraudulent_volume_eur,
    ROUND(
      SUM(CASE WHEN has_fraudulent_dispute THEN eur_amount ELSE 0.0 END)
      / NULLIF(SUM(eur_amount), 0.0)
      * 100.0,
      1
    ) AS fraud_rate_PERCENT
  FROM cte_tx
  GROUP BY 1, 2
),
cte_latest AS (
  SELECT
    merchant,
    month,
    total_volume_eur,
    fraudulent_volume_eur,
    fraud_rate_PERCENT
  FROM cte_fraud_per_month
  ORDER BY month DESC
  LIMIT 1
)
SELECT
  CASE
    WHEN COALESCE(fraud_rate_PERCENT, 0.0) >= 7.7 THEN 'yes'
    ELSE 'no'
  END AS is_in_danger_of_high_fraud_rate_fine
FROM cte_latest
```
